# Tilawa Dart — goal-driven verification

Follow [karpathy-guidelines.mdc](karpathy-guidelines.mdc) for all Dart work.

## Before coding

- Read surrounding code in the same feature (`presentation/`, `domain/`,
  `data/`).
- State assumptions (screen, platform, breaking vs additive change).
- Prefer the smallest change; no drive-by refactors.

## Success criteria (run from `apps/tilawa/` unless noted)

| Change type | Verify |
|-------------|--------|
| Logic / cubit / repository | `flutter test test/features/<feature>/` |
| UI widget | Widget test in mirrored `test/` path |
| Router / DI registration | `dart analyze` + affected feature tests |
| `packages/ui_kit` or `packages/core` | `dart analyze` in that package + app tests that use it |

```sh
dart analyze
flutter test test/features/<feature>
```

## Tilawa constraints (surgical)

- **Bloc/Cubit**, **get_it**, **GoRouter**, **`Either<Failure, T>`** — no new
  patterns without request.
- **Tokens**: `theme.tokens`, `theme.componentTokens`, `theme.colorScheme` —
  no hard-coded sizes/colors.
- **Strings**: `context.l10n` in presentation only.
- **TilawaCard**: conflicting actions → sibling `Row`, not nested controls
  (see `CLAUDE.md`).

## Done when

Analyzer clean, targeted tests pass, and every changed line traces to the
request.
